&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wexham Park Emergency Department (ED) has been rated ‘outstanding’ by the Care Quality Commission (CQC).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Frimley Health NHS Foundation Trust has an exciting new ED that opened its doors in Spring 2019, which includes a new Paediatric Emergency Department (PED) with our own resus and trauma bay. Along with advanced medical equipment and a bigger environment, we will be the largest PED within the county.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Wexham Park PED, patient safety and effective patient care is our priority. Presently our PED see approximately one third of the patients that present to ED. We are looking to recruit paediatric staff nurses who are enthusiastic and motivated about emergency medicine. You will work with patients and their families; caring for children with minor injuries and illness, as well as paediatric traumas, and the critically unwell child in resus. Our nurses have the opportunities to attend in-house training programmes, these include, safeguarding training, domestic abuse, plastering/suturing, venepuncture/cannulation and IV training. Other courses available are the High Dependency module, Mentorship course, PILS and EPLS/APLS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity to develop our nursing workforce. We are passionate about emergency medicine, and within the department we work closely with Adult ED, nurse practitioners and paediatric services. If a career in emergency medicine is for you, then come and join our exceptional team on the front line to make positive changes to patient care in our Paediatric ED. You would be joining a team that is friendly and passionate about paediatric emergency medicine and are dedicated to working together in raising standards and improving patient care. You will be supported and encouraged to progress within the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Charlotte Carwardine&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;charlotte.carwardine@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01753 633788&lt;/p&gt;
